==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Weald
<hw>Weald</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. See
<er>Wold</er>.]</ety> <def>A wood or forest; a wooded land or region;
also, an open country; -- often used in place names.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fled all night long by glimmering waste and <qex>weald</qex>,⟦br⟧
And heard the spirits of the waste and <qex>weald</qex>⟦br⟧
Moan as she fled.</q> <rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Weald clay</b></col> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>, <cd>the
uppermost member of the Wealden strata. See
<er>Wealden</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wealden</ent>⟦br⟧
